OpenGrid developer overview
When you clone the opengrid repository to your computer, you get the following file structure
(some files are omitted):
Source for documentation. Built documentation is
excluded from the source code repo.
Contains only notebooks. These are used as demos
and tutorials for all the functionality in opengrid.
To start a notebook server: open a terminal in this folder and type
jupyter notebook. The ideal place for starting with opengrid!
The python package 'opengrid'. Contains 3 submodules:
config contains both source code, passwords/passfiles
and your personal opengrid.cfg file.
Create your opengrid.cfg file based on the opengrid.cfg.example.
Never publish or commit your config file, it contains passwords.
library contains all the core functionality (except configuration).
There are submodules for houseprint, analysis, ...
recipes contains python files that can be run as jobs.
Opengrid speaks docker! Build a stable or development
docker image and fire it with these files.
Configuration for respectively the code coverage computation,
gitignore and the build and automated testing on TravisCI
All python dependencies.
Install them at once with pip install -r requirements.txt
Opengrid uses the Apache 2.0 license.
